  "prompt": "Where can I watch the first Fox News/Facebook 2016 Republican primary debate after it's over?",
  "response": "The first Fox News/Facebook 2016 Republican primary debate, which took place on August 6, 2015, can be watched online through various platforms. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **Fox News Website**: Fox News typically makes the debate available for streaming on their website. You can visit the Fox News website and look for the debate in their video section.\n\n2. **YouTube**: Fox News often uploads the full debate to their official YouTube channel. You can search for \"Fox News Republican primary debate August 6, 2015\" on YouTube to find it.\n\n3. **Fox News App**: The Fox News app for mobile devices may also have the debate available for streaming.\n\n4. **Cable and Satellite TV Providers**: Some cable and satellite TV providers offer on-demand access to Fox News programming, including past debates.\n\nPlease note that availability may vary depending on your location and the specific platform's content policies.",
